{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Over 60s should retake their theory and practical driving test every ten years",
        "additional_details": "After people start hitting a certain age their motor skill and cognitive skills reduce and their reaction time lessens we think if we can catch those things a little earlier while they retaking their theory and practical tests then it would benefit a lot of road users, it could stop a lot of accidents and collisions happening. \r\n\r\nThere have been a lot of new vehicles regulations and I would also say a lot of the theory has changed too. \r\n\r\nThis is for the safety of the public.",
        "background": "For safety reasons for themselves and others on the road we think over 60s should have to retake their theory and practical driving test every ten years, 60-70-80 and 90 years of age.",
